Create a reusable UI emphora named emphora using:
- HTML (emphora.html — contains ONLY <emphora> tag, no body/head/scripts)
- SCSS (emphora.scss)
- Vanilla JavaScript (emphora.js)
- Bootstrap 5
- Modern Material Design, Material Design icons and styles
- Always create a JS class for emphora and initialize it inside the JS file itself

Rules:
- The emphora is wrapped in a display:block element <emphora class="emphora">
- The root element uses .emphora
- All styles must be scoped to .emphora
- No global styles or IDs
- Publish click events using wc.publish
- Subscribe to all 4 emphora events using wc.subscribe
- Create a onMessage function to be passed to wc.subscribe
- All published (wc.publish) messages must be logged using wc.log to console before being published
- MUST WAIT for element to be available inside DOM via MutationObserver (supports <wc-include>)
- Fully responsive (mostly used on mobile)

Data:
- JSON driven — all data comes from emphora.config.js

Files:
- emphora.config.js — single source of truth for ALL data, config, labels, endpoints, passwords, ports, dashboards
- emphora.scss — SCSS source only, never compiled CSS
- emphora.html — ONLY the <emphora>…</emphora> tag, nothing else
- emphora.js — Emphora class + EmAdmin class + wc bus
- server.js — Node.js + sql.js backend
- admin.html — Admin dashboard (accountType: admin)
- employee.html — Employee/Professional dashboard
- employer.html — Employer dashboard
- researcher.html — Researcher dashboard
- users.html — Full user management table

Backend:
- Node.js + sql.js (pure WASM SQLite, no native compilation)
- Port: 3001 (auto-increments if busy, defined in config)
- Apache reverse proxy at emphora.melify.com → localhost:3001

Auth:
- JWT + bcrypt sessions stored in SQLite
- Login, register, logout, profile endpoints
- is_active flag blocks login when disabled

Seed accounts (all password: test-1234):
- admin@emphora.dev      — accountType: admin
- employee@emphora.dev   — accountType: employee
- employer@emphora.dev   — accountType: employer
- researcher@emphora.dev — accountType: researcher
- Seed re-syncs passwords on every server restart

Account types: employee | employer | researcher | admin

On login → redirect to role dashboard:
- admin      → admin.html
- employee   → employee.html
- employer   → employer.html
- researcher → researcher.html
- User saved to sessionStorage as 'emphora_user'
- Logout → redirect to /

Components:
- Registration form (firstName, lastName, email, password, confirmPassword, accountType chips, terms)
- Login form
- Light/dark mode toggle (persisted to localStorage)
- Account type tag in card header (updates live on chip select)
- Password strength meter
- Dev tools bar REMOVED — login now via users.html one-click login
- Admin panel (EmAdmin class) — inline modal with user list, add/edit/enable/disable/delete

users.html:
- Full CRUD user table (search, filter by type/status/verified, sortable columns)
- One-click "Login as" per row (uses test-1234 for seed accounts, prompts for others)
- ← Admin back button (visible only to admin accountType users)
- Add user modal, Edit modal, Enable/Disable, Delete with confirm

admin.html:
- Purple admin theme
- Live stats: total users, employees, employers, disabled, active sessions
- Recent users table
- Account breakdown bars
- "View Users" button → users.html
- Sign Out → /

Accessibility:
- Semantic HTML, keyboard accessible, visible focus states, ADA compliant
- aria-live regions, aria-label, aria-required, aria-invalid throughout

Restrictions:
- No frameworks in frontend
- Vanilla JavaScript only
- No compiled CSS output — SCSS source files only
- Always remember mtk- prefix convention
- Always show updated code in FULL
